<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 25. Geographical distribution map of the genus Gastrocentrum." , "Figure 14. A-C Gastrocentrum magnum sp. nov. female, paratype from Assam A pygidium B sixth ventrite C female reproductive organ D Gastrocentrum dux from Australia, female reproductive organ. Abbreviations: ali alimentary canal bc bursa copulatrix cov common oviduct olb oblique bacculi ovp ovipositor sp spermatheca spg spermathecal gland spgtt top tail of spermathecal gland spglt lateral tail of spermathecal gland va vagina vtb ventral bacculi. Scale bar: 1 mm." , "Figure 10. Drawing of elytral asetiferous punctations. A Gastrocentrum magnum sp. nov. B G. dux C G. regulare sp. nov. D G. xiaodongi sp. nov. E G. gaoligongense sp. nov. F-H G. zayuense sp. nov. The numbers 1 - 10 annotate the serial rows of primary asetiferous punctuations (PAP). Abbreviations: a accessory asetiferous punctations." , "Figures 1 - 9. Habitus. 1 Gastrocentrum magnum sp. nov. Holotype 2 G. dux from Australia 3 G. unicolor (Lectotype of G. pauper) 4 G. regulare sp. nov. Holotype 5 G. xiaodongi sp. nov. Holotype 6 G. zayuense sp. nov. Holotype 7 G. gaoligongense sp. nov. Holotype 8 Tillus nitidus comb. nov. Holotype 9 Isocymatodera atricolor Syntype. Scale bars: 5 mm (1, 2) 2 mm (3 - 9)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467732" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467722" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467718" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467717" .

